This paper deals with the comparison of two types of neural networks, Deep Echo State Networks (DeepESNs) and gated Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs), on multivariate time-series prediction tasks. This work involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on signal processing and prediction, which could fall under the cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) sub-category. The use of neural networks for prediction tasks also relates to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. The paper also mentions the efficiency and accuracy of the models, which could be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of multiple time-scales dynamics, which could be relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
